race.comment: Competitive. Linda Meech rides and trains THE DAILY PLANET (4), who is ready to win off a 1.7L defeat at Murray Bridge. He will be looking to secure a soft run from the inside gate and he's still shy of his best. Has the tongue tie on for the first time. REAL ALLIANCE (3) will improve today and ran her best race at the provincials over a mile. Has placed 2/3 second up and is likely to be finishing hard. TUNDRA (5) runs along and followed a 1L defeat first up with a near miss at St Arnaud. Gets some weight relief and draws inside. Fitter and has claims. DON'T TELL SHERIFF (8) brings good form from the non-TABs. Will carry a feather this level with a 3kg claim atop, and he shouldn't be taken lightly.
